-- Azarenka Wins Second Set Against Williams, Evens U.S. Open Final
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-09-09T22:10:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-09/azarenka-wins-second-set-against-williams-evens-u-s-open-final.html
Top-seeded Victoria Azarenka of
Belarus won the second set of the U.S. Open women’s final 6-2
against Serena Williams, evening the match at one set apiece and
sending it to a decisive third set.  Williams, a fourth-seeded American and three-time champion,
won the first set 6-2.  It is the first three-set women’s final since 1995 at the
U.S. Open, when  Steffi Graf  defeated Monica Seles.  Azarenka has a 12-0 record in three-set matches this year.
Williams is 6-1 in three-setters in 2012.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
